article.headline: Manhattan skirts past Morgan State 73-69
article.story: RIVERDALE, N.Y. -- Shane Richards scored 20 points and made four free throws on one trip to spark Manhattan's late run past Morgan State 73-69 on Saturday night. Morgan State's Blake Bozeman was called for a personal foul and technical foul on the same play with 3:02 left, sending Richards to the foul line. Richards tied the game by making all four and sparked a 12-4 run to close out the game. Tyler Wilson gave Manhattan (3-7) the lead for good with a layup on the Jaspers' next possession and they made 4 of 6 free throws in the final 30 seconds. Emmy Andujar added 16 points, six assists and five rebounds for Manhattan and broke a scoring drought of over six minutes on a layup with 4:25 to go. Morgan State (2-10) added five straight points after Andujar's layup to complete a 12-2 run, leading 65-61. Zech Smith led the Bears with 19 points and 15 rebounds.
